vobcopy: vobcopy (copy (rip) files from a dvd to the harddisk)
vobcopy:
vobcopy: vobcopy copies DVD .vob files to harddisk (thanks to libdvdread)
vobcopy: and merges them into file(s) with the name extracted from the DVD.
vobcopy: It checks for enough free space on the destination drive and
vobcopy: compares the copied size to the size on DVD (in case the size is
vobcopy: wrong the files keep the .partial ending ). It should definitely
vobcopy: work on linux and now on FreeBSD, OpenBSD, NetBSD, Solaris and
vobcopy: MacOSX too!
